Description: Rim fragment of a small pottery vessel (oinochoe? jar?); coverend in cream slip inside and out, raised ridge around neck, flaring mouth, dark red horizontal stripe in concave zone between. Porous, red clay, Munsell 2.5YR 5/6 (red).
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 319)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
